UnnecessaryModifier.description:
Description

Fields in interfaces and annotations are automaticallypublic static final, and methods arepublic abstract.
Classes, interfaces or annotations nested in an interface or annotation are automaticallypublic static(all nested interfaces and annotations are automatically static).
Nested enums are automaticallystatic.
For historical reasons, modifiers which are implied by the context are accepted by the compiler, but are superfluous.

Example(s):

Use this rule by referencing it:
UnnecessaryModifier.option: This rule has no specific options.
